name: Witch-Winds at Intendance
description: Blue hour descends upon Anse Intendance as sea mist rolls across the shore break. A weathered pirate helmsman clutches a brass lantern with five panes of glass, its amber light cutting through the gathering gloom. Behind him in the surf foam, a witch in a tattered shawl traces spiral runes with her fingertips, calling upon the ancient winds. Seven perfect spirals bloom in the foam where witch-craft meets tide, while the lantern's five panes catch the last light. Bearing 57°. Cipher output: LA. "When the sea writes a spiral, count the panes that brave it."

name: Baie Lazare Oath
description: Golden hour bathes Baie Lazare in warm amber light as a grizzled pirate captain stands before the stone memorial that bears the name of Lazare Picault. The witch beside him ties gris-gris charms to a weathered post while distant sails dot the bay. A single coin gleams outside the open chest clasp, but look closer to the dagger thrust into the rock—its blade tilts at precisely 124 degrees of reverence carved in steel and stone. Bearing 124°. Cipher output: ZA. "Tilt the blade as he once did; the angle names the bay."

name: Anse Gaulette Whisper
description: Midnight settles over Anse Gaulette like a velvet shroud, broken only by bands of ground fog that drift across the shore. A black cat with emerald eyes perches atop a rope-bound chest, its gaze fixed on some unseen presence beyond the veil. Three stars gleam from its collar—celestial markers that align with the cardinal directions of West, South, and East. Bearing 202°. Cipher output: RE. "Choose the middle star where fog eats sound."

name: Police Bay Warding
description: The noon sun blazes overhead as strong trade winds whip Police Bay into a frenzy of white-capped rollers. Two weathered pirates strain against a mast-spar while a witch traces protective veve symbols in the sand. Crossed cutlasses lie embedded in the sand, their shadows falling at angles that speak in numbers—a 2 here, a 6 there, clear as day to those who can read the language of steel and sun. Bearing 226°. Cipher output: PI. "Shadowed steel counts truer than the sun."

name: Cap Ternay Sounding
description: Dawn breaks over Cap Ternay in gentle haze, painting the marine park headlands in soft pastels. A pirate sounder works his lead line with practiced precision while a witch holds a conch shell to her ear, listening for the ocean's ancient secrets. The sounding line tells a deeper story—knotted at intervals of 3, 5, and 8, the sacred sequence of living growth. Bearing 158°. Cipher output: CA. "Hear the sea count in steps of living growth."

name: Rock Pool Charm
description: Late afternoon sunlight filters through the mist at Port Glaud Rock Pool, creating ethereal shafts that dance across the calm water. A witch perches upon a massive boulder, raising a lantern high while a pirate kneels studying a cipher scrap. Carved into the rock face, a spiral of coins winds seven perfect turns before disappearing into a skull etching. Bearing 187°. Cipher output: UL. "Where still water spills, the spiral names the way."

name: Sauzier's Fall Sign
description: Midday spray catches the light as Sauzier Waterfall thunders down the granite face in Port Glaud's hidden valley. The witch and pirate stand side by side on the wet ledge while ancient runes carved deep into the rock face remain worn but legible. Three runic arrows point East, South, East—their directions averaging to 110 degrees. Bearing 110°. Cipher output: TE. "Three arrows fall, one bearing stands."

name: Mission Lodge Veil
description: Sunset paints the stone arches of Mission Lodge in shades of amber and gold while mist pools in the valleys below. A witch's veil billows across the ancient compass ring etched into the central arch while a pirate adjusts his sextant with practiced precision. The sextant reads 23 degrees—the angle of the tropic, the measure of earth's tilt. Bearing 233°. Cipher output: LT. "At the ridge of lost voices, measure what the sun forgets."

name: Copolia Sky
description: Morning light breaks through low clouds as the granite dome of Copolia pierces the sky. Far below, Victoria spreads across the coastal plain while a witch sprinkles coarse salt into the wind. Her companion drives a dagger through a parchment map, pinning their position—the dagger points northeast at exactly 045 degrees. Bearing 45°. Cipher output: AN. "Pin the map where the cloud thins to glass."

name: Morne Blanc Watch
description: Late morning brightness floods the viewpoint of Morne Blanc as layered ridges cascade toward the distant sea. The pirate extends his spyglass toward the horizon while a witch traces mystical circles in the silver-green lichen. The compass card beside her bears four cardinal directions, but the eastern point has vanished—what's missing speaks louder than what remains. Bearing 261°. Cipher output: SE. "What's missing points harder than what remains."

name: Anse Major Passage
description: Afternoon glare transforms Anse Major into a cauldron of blazing silver. A pirate strains against the corner of a heavy chest while a witch marks the traditional 'X' on a weathered granite slab. A black cat sits in perfect stillness, its emerald eyes watching—two rope coils, two eyes, and the bearing arrow sketched at 222 degrees. Bearing 222°. Cipher output: GA. "Two coils, two eyes; follow the double."

name: Eden Channel Lights
description: Night falls over Victoria harbor like a velvet curtain studded with diamonds. The channel sparkles with harbor lights that mirror the constellations above, creating a double sky. A pirate leans against the rail while a witch cups a small flame, revealing ancient runes. Three lanterns hang at different heights—their morse pattern spells 'A' in light and shadow. Bearing 278°. Cipher output: UL. "Where man's stars mirror heaven's, read the shorter song."

name: Moyenne Graves
description: Dawn breaks over Moyenne Island with hushed reverence befitting a sacred place where forgotten pirates rest beneath simple stone markers. A weathered pirate kneels before one of the graves while the witch places a skull-coin upon the weathered stone. Rosary-like beads tell their silent story in the rhythm of prayer: one bead, three beads, two beads. Bearing 196°. Cipher output: ET. "Count what's prayed, not what's carved."

name: Cerf's Narrow
description: Midday sun blazes as a stiff breeze churns the narrow channel between Mahé and Cerf Island into a maze of coral shallows. The pirate steers with practiced precision while a witch casts salt into their wake. A small skull flag snaps in the wind while the dagger lashed across the tiller holds steady at 304 degrees. Bearing 304°. Cipher output: TA. "Hold the tiller where coral bites blue."

name: Anse Royale Rune
description: Sunset bathes Anse Royale in golden light as calm waters lap against the shore. A beach shrine rises from carefully arranged driftwood while the witch paints runes in colors that seem to glow. A pirate lays coins in the pattern of a cross—one short, three long, forming the ratio 1:3. Black cat prints mark the sand in four perfect impressions. Bearing 143°. Cipher output: LA. "Four steps, a crooked cross—the shorter arm is the truth."

name: Baie Lazare Lantern Line
description: Night settles over Baie Lazare with thin fog as five lanterns are staked along the shore. A pirate counts while a witch points to the ridge. The lantern spacing spells 2-1-2 in a wide-narrow-wide pattern, pointing WNW at approximately 292 degrees. A skull sits guard on the center post. Bearing 292°. Cipher output: ZA. "Where five lights breathe, follow the wider path."

name: Anse Soleil Cross-Sea
description: Morning breaks over Anse Soleil with crisp glare that transforms the yellow sand into molten gold. A pirate stretches a line from headland to headland while a witch hangs a powerful charm at the midpoint. The rope bears seven knots, each tied with the precision of a master navigator—from PICAULT, take the seventh letter. Bearing 207°. Cipher output: RE. "Span the yellow sea with seven holds."

name: Takamaka Sign
description: Late afternoon settles over Takamaka with salt haze that makes the giant takamaka tree seem even more mystical. A witch nails a bright ribbon to the root formations while a pirate carves a small compass into the living bark. The compass points at 169 degrees while the ribbon with three holes breathes in the wind. Bearing 169°. Cipher output: PI. "The root points where the ribbon breathes."

name: Lazare Picault View
description: Sunset transforms the Lazare Picault viewpoint into a cathedral of light and color where the ridge above Anse Boileau commands a vista to the horizon. A pirate and witch stand together in silhouette while a large compass ring overlays the entire scene. The sun settles at the 255-degree mark with tiny letters 'LP' etched nearby. Bearing 255°. Cipher output: CA. "Name the man the ridge remembers."

name: Gaulette Night Oath
description: Midnight settles over Anse Gaulette like the final page of an ancient tome, bringing low fog and starlight. The final chest lies half-buried while a witch lifts her veil with ceremony and a pirate plants the flag with solemnity. Faint runes shimmer across the surf spelling 'ANSE GAULETTE' when starlight catches them just so. Bearing 320°. Cipher output: UL. "Read the sea left to right; breathe when the tide holds its breath."

name: S3-01 — Landing at Anse Gaulette
description: S3-01 — Landing at Anse Gaulette. Clue: Where Picault kissed the shore, the rope points past the teeth of granite.

name: S3-02 — Skull in the Sand
description: S3-02 — Skull in the Sand. Clue: Count the coins to the water’s edge; the odd piece marks your bearing.

name: S3-03 — Rune of Ros Sodyer
description: S3-03 — Rune of Ros Sodyer. Clue: When the ocean exhales, three lights remain—read them in the pool’s quiet eye.

name: S3-04 — Torch Wall at Cascade
description: S3-04 — Torch Wall at Cascade. Clue: Step through the veil—fire reveals the mark the rain conceals.

name: S3-05 — Parrot of Mission Lodge
description: S3-05 — Parrot of Mission Lodge. Clue: The arch’s shadow names the hour; the feather points your climb.

name: S3-06 — Granite Teeth of Georgette
description: S3-06 — Granite Teeth of Georgette. Clue: Between the teeth, a corner of night; measure the gaps to find the shoal.

name: S3-07 — Vache Sentinel
description: S3-07 — Vache Sentinel. Clue: A cow by name, a watch by duty—seven lights refuse to drink.

name: S3-08 — Intendance Thunder
description: S3-08 — Intendance Thunder. Clue: Turn the scar on the coin toward calm; the shoreline will forgive.

name: S3-09 — Royale Lantern
description: S3-09 — Royale Lantern. Clue: Royale rests with two small lights—loop the rope and climb to counsel.

name: S3-10 — La Misère Lookout
description: S3-10 — La Misère Lookout. Clue: Count two knots of wind and drop to the quiet bay.

name: S3-11 — Baie Ternay Mirror
description: S3-11 — Baie Ternay Mirror. Clue: In a bay that refuses storm, the coral fingers name your number.

name: S3-12 — Anse Major Edge
description: S3-12 — Anse Major Edge. Clue: Count the cuts along the hilt—the path bites east.

name: S3-13 — Morne Blanc Mist
description: S3-13 — Morne Blanc Mist. Clue: Five lights survive the cloud; lay your arc where the ridge breathes.

name: S3-14 — Copolia Dome
description: S3-14 — Copolia Dome. Clue: On the stone, light bends the reef—arc the rope where shoreline turns.

name: S3-15 — Sauzier’s Echo
description: S3-15 — Sauzier’s Echo. Clue: Follow the echo’s measure; its bars climb the coast.

name: S3-16 — Skull Mark at Gaulettes
description: S3-16 — Skull Mark at Gaulettes. Clue: Scratch the sign and follow the feather—the coin’s notch faces home.

name: S3-17 — Denison Reef Gate
description: S3-17 — Denison Reef Gate. Clue: Six lights pretend to open—turn your bow; home holds the lock.

name: S3-18 — Curieuse Mangrove Secret
description: S3-18 — Curieuse Mangrove Secret. Clue: Where roots breathe air, a small chest lies listening.

name: S3-19 — Anse Source d’Argent Veil
description: S3-19 — Anse Source d’Argent Veil. Clue: The rose chalked on stone turns with the sun—trace its shadow to the gap.

name: S3-20 — Door Below Morne Seychellois
description: S3-20 — Door Below Morne Seychellois. Clue: All roads return to the first shore; the door hears only the right order.
